530 static MCRegister convertFPR32ToFPR64(MCRegister Reg) { 0

535 // Attempts to match Name as a register (either using the default name or ----
536 // alternative ABI names), setting RegNo to the matching register. Upon ----
537 // failure, returns true and sets RegNo to 0. ----
538 static bool matchRegisterNameHelper(MCRegister &RegNo, StringRef Name) { 0
539 RegNo = MatchRegisterName(Name); 0
540 // The 32-bit and 64-bit FPRs have the same asm name. Check that the initial ----
541 // match always matches the 32-bit variant, and not the 64-bit one. ----
542 assert(!(RegNo >= LoongArch::F0_64 && RegNo <= LoongArch::F31_64)); 0
543 // The default FPR register class is based on the tablegen enum ordering. ----
544 static_assert(LoongArch::F0 < LoongArch::F0_64, ----
545 "FPR matching must be updated"); ----
546 if (RegNo == LoongArch::NoRegister) 0
547 RegNo = MatchRegisterAltName(Name); 0
548 ----
549 return RegNo == LoongArch::NoRegister; 0
550 } ----

552 bool LoongArchAsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
553 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
554 return Error(getLoc(), "invalid register number"); 0

562 ----
563 bool LoongArchAsmParser::classifySymbolRef(const MCExpr *Expr, 0
564 LoongArchMCExpr::VariantKind &Kind) { ----
565 Kind = LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_None; 0
566 ----
567 if (const LoongArchMCExpr *RE = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
568 Kind = RE->getKind(); 0
569 Expr = RE->getSubExpr(); 0
570 } ----
571 ----
572 MCValue Res; 0
573 if (Expr->evaluateAsRelocatable(Res, nullptr, nullptr)) 0
574 return Res.getRefKind() == LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_None; 0
575 return false; 0
576 } ----
577 ----
578 ParseStatus LoongArchAsmParser::parseRegister(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
579 if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Dollar)) 0
580 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
581 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) 0
582 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
583 ----
584 StringRef Name = getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
585 MCRegister RegNo; 0
586 matchRegisterNameHelper(RegNo, Name); 0
587 if (RegNo == LoongArch::NoRegister) 0
588 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
589 ----
590 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
591 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Name.size()); 0
592 getLexer().Lex(); 0
593 Operands.push_back(LoongArchOperand::createReg(RegNo, S, E)); 0
594 ----
595 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
596 } ----
597 ----
598 ParseStatus LoongArchAsmParser::parseImmediate(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
599 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
600 SMLoc E; 0
601 const MCExpr *Res; ----
602 ----
603 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
604 default: 0
605 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
606 case AsmToken::LParen: 0
607 case AsmToken::Dot: ----
608 case AsmToken::Minus: ----
609 case AsmToken::Plus: ----
610 case AsmToken::Exclaim: ----
611 case AsmToken::Tilde: ----
612 case AsmToken::Integer: ----
613 case AsmToken::String: ----
614 case AsmToken::Identifier: ----
615 if (getParser().parseExpression(Res, E)) 0
616 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
617 break; 0
618 case AsmToken::Percent: 0
619 return parseOperandWithModifier(Operands); 0
620 } ----
621 ----
622 Operands.push_back(LoongArchOperand::createImm(Res, S, E)); 0
623 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
624 } ----
625 ----
626 ParseStatus ----
627 LoongArchAsmParser::parseOperandWithModifier(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
628 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
629 SMLoc E; 0
630 ----
631 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Percent) 0
632 return Error(getLoc(), "expected '%' for operand modifier"); 0
633 ----
634 getParser().Lex(); // Eat '%' 0
635 ----
636 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) 0
637 return Error(getLoc(), "expected valid identifier for operand modifier"); 0
638 StringRef Identifier = getParser().getTok().getIdentifier(); 0
639 LoongArchMCExpr::VariantKind VK = ----
640 LoongArchMCExpr::getVariantKindForName(Identifier); 0
641 if (VK == LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_Invalid) 0
642 return Error(getLoc(), "unrecognized operand modifier"); 0
643 ----
644 getParser().Lex(); // Eat the identifier 0
645 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::LParen) 0
646 return Error(getLoc(), "expected '('"); 0
647 getParser().Lex(); // Eat '(' 0
648 ----
649 const MCExpr *SubExpr; ----
650 if (getParser().parseParenExpression(SubExpr, E)) 0
651 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
652 ----
653 const MCExpr *ModExpr = LoongArchMCExpr::create(SubExpr, VK, getContext()); 0
654 Operands.push_back(LoongArchOperand::createImm(ModExpr, S, E)); 0
655 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
656 } ----
657 ----
658 ParseStatus LoongArchAsmParser::parseSImm26Operand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
659 SMLoc S = getLoc(); 0
660 const MCExpr *Res; ----
661 ----
662 if (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::Percent) 0
663 return parseOperandWithModifier(Operands); 0
664 ----
665 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Identifier) 0
666 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
667 ----
668 StringRef Identifier; 0
669 if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
670 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
671 ----
672 SMLoc E = SMLoc::getFromPointer(S.getPointer() + Identifier.size()); 0
673 ----
674 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Identifier); 0
675 Res = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, getContext()); 0
676 Res = LoongArchMCExpr::create(Res, LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_CALL, 0
677 getContext()); ----
678 Operands.push_back(LoongArchOperand::createImm(Res, S, E)); 0
679 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
680 } ----
681 ----
682 ParseStatus LoongArchAsmParser::parseAtomicMemOp(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
683 // Parse "$r*". ----
684 if (!parseRegister(Operands).isSuccess()) 0
685 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
686 ----
687 // If there is a next operand and it is 0, ignore it. Otherwise print a ----
688 // diagnostic message. ----
689 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
690 int64_t ImmVal; ----
691 SMLoc ImmStart = getLoc(); 0
692 if (getParser().parseIntToken(ImmVal, "expected optional integer offset")) 0
693 return ParseStatus::Failure; 0
694 if (ImmVal) 0
695 return Error(ImmStart, "optional integer offset must be 0"); 0
696 } ----
697 ----
698 return ParseStatus::Success; 0
699 } ----
700 /// Looks at a token type and creates the relevant operand from this ----
701 /// information, adding to Operands. Return true upon an error. ----
702 bool LoongArchAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, 0
703 StringRef Mnemonic) { ----
704 // Check if the current operand has a custom associated parser, if so, try to ----
705 // custom parse the operand, or fallback to the general approach. ----
706 ParseStatus Result = ----
707 MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic, /*ParseForAllFeatures=*/true); 0
708 if (Result.isSuccess()) 0
709 return false; 0
710 if (Result.isFailure()) 0
711 return true; 0
712 ----
713 if (parseRegister(Operands).isSuccess() || 0
714 parseImmediate(Operands).isSuccess()) 0
715 return false; 0
716 ----
717 // Finally we have exhausted all options and must declare defeat. ----
718 return Error(getLoc(), "unknown operand"); 0
719 } ----
720 ----
721 bool LoongArchAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, 0
722 StringRef Name, SMLoc NameLoc, ----
723 OperandVector &Operands) { ----
724 // First operand in MCInst is instruction mnemonic. ----
725 Operands.push_back(LoongArchOperand::createToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
726 ----
727 // If there are no more operands, then finish. ----
728 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) 0
729 return false; 0
730 ----
731 // Parse first operand. ----
732 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) 0
733 return true; 0
734 ----
735 // Parse until end of statement, consuming commas between operands. ----
736 while (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) 0
737 if (parseOperand(Operands, Name)) 0
738 return true; 0
739 ----
740 // Parse end of statement and return successfully. ----
741 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) 0
742 return false; 0
743 ----
744 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
745 getParser().eatToEndOfStatement(); 0
746 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
747 } ----
748 ----
749 void LoongArchAsmParser::emitLAInstSeq(MCRegister DestReg, MCRegister TmpReg, 0
750 const MCExpr *Symbol, ----
751 SmallVectorImpl &Insts, ----
752 SMLoc IDLoc, MCStreamer &Out) { ----
753 MCContext &Ctx = getContext(); 0
754 for (LoongArchAsmParser::Inst &Inst : Insts) { 0
755 unsigned Opc = Inst.Opc; 0
756 LoongArchMCExpr::VariantKind VK = Inst.VK; 0
757 const LoongArchMCExpr *LE = LoongArchMCExpr::create(Symbol, VK, Ctx); 0
758 switch (Opc) { 0
759 default: 0
760 llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode"); 0
761 case LoongArch::PCALAU12I: 0
762 case LoongArch::LU12I_W: ----
763 Out.emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(Opc).addReg(DestReg).addExpr(LE), 0
764 getSTI()); ----
765 break; 0
766 case LoongArch::ORI: 0
767 case LoongArch::ADDI_W: ----
768 case LoongArch::LD_W: ----
769 case LoongArch::LD_D: { ----
770 if (VK == LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_None) { 0
771 Out.emitInstruction( 0
772 MCInstBuilder(Opc).addReg(DestReg).addReg(DestReg).addImm(0), 0
773 getSTI()); ----
774 continue; 0
775 } ----
776 Out.emitInstruction( 0
777 MCInstBuilder(Opc).addReg(DestReg).addReg(DestReg).addExpr(LE), 0
778 getSTI()); ----
779 break; 0
780 } ----
781 case LoongArch::LU32I_D: 0
782 Out.emitInstruction(MCInstBuilder(Opc) 0
783 .addReg(DestReg == TmpReg ? DestReg : TmpReg) 0
784 .addReg(DestReg == TmpReg ? DestReg : TmpReg) 0
785 .addExpr(LE), 0
786 getSTI()); ----
787 break; 0
788 case LoongArch::LU52I_D: 0
789 Out.emitInstruction( 0
790 MCInstBuilder(Opc).addReg(TmpReg).addReg(TmpReg).addExpr(LE), 0
791 getSTI()); ----
792 break; 0
793 case LoongArch::ADDI_D: 0
794 Out.emitInstruction( 0
795 MCInstBuilder(Opc) 0
796 .addReg(TmpReg) 0
797 .addReg(DestReg == TmpReg ? TmpReg : LoongArch::R0) 0
798 .addExpr(LE), 0
799 getSTI()); ----
800 break; 0
801 case LoongArch::ADD_D: 0
802 case LoongArch::LDX_D: ----
803 Out.emitInstruction( 0
804 MCInstBuilder(Opc).addReg(DestReg).addReg(DestReg).addReg(TmpReg), 0
805 getSTI()); ----
806 break; 0
807 } ----
808 } ----
809 } 0
810 ----
811 void LoongArchAsmParser::emitLoadAddressAbs(MCInst &Inst, SMLoc IDLoc, 0
812 MCStreamer &Out) { ----
813 // la.abs $rd, sym ----
814 // expands to: ----
815 // lu12i.w $rd, %abs_hi20(sym) ----
816 // ori $rd, $rd, %abs_lo12(sym) ----
817 // ----
818 // for 64bit appends: ----
819 // lu32i.d $rd, %abs64_lo20(sym) ----
820 // lu52i.d $rd, $rd, %abs64_hi12(sym) ----
821 MCRegister DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
822 const MCExpr *Symbol = Inst.getOpcode() == LoongArch::PseudoLA_ABS 0
823 ? Inst.getOperand(1).getExpr() 0
824 : Inst.getOperand(2).getExpr(); 0
825 InstSeq Insts; 0
826 ----
827 Insts.push_back(LoongArchAsmParser::Inst( 0
828 LoongArch::LU12I_W, LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_ABS_HI20)); ----
829 Insts.push_back(LoongArchAsmParser::Inst( 0
830 LoongArch::ORI, LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_ABS_LO12)); ----
831 ----
832 if (is64Bit()) { 0
833 Insts.push_back(LoongArchAsmParser::Inst( 0
834 LoongArch::LU32I_D, LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_ABS64_LO20)); ----
835 Insts.push_back(LoongArchAsmParser::Inst( 0
836 LoongArch::LU52I_D, LoongArchMCExpr::VK_LoongArch_ABS64_HI12)); ----
837 } ----
838 ----
839 emitLAInstSeq(DestReg, DestReg, Symbol, Insts, IDLoc, Out); 0
840 } 0

1165 unsigned LoongArchAsmParser::checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) { 0
1166 unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode(); 0
1167 switch (Opc) { 0
1168 default: 0
1169 if (Opc >= LoongArch::AMADD_D && Opc <= LoongArch::AMXOR_W) { 0
1170 unsigned Rd = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1171 unsigned Rk = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1172 unsigned Rj = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1173 if ((Rd == Rk || Rd == Rj) && Rd != LoongArch::R0) 0
1174 return Match_RequiresAMORdDifferRkRj; 0
1175 } ----
1176 break; 0
1177 case LoongArch::PseudoLA_PCREL_LARGE: 0
1178 case LoongArch::PseudoLA_GOT_LARGE: ----
1179 case LoongArch::PseudoLA_TLS_IE_LARGE: ----
1180 case LoongArch::PseudoLA_TLS_LD_LARGE: ----
1181 case LoongArch::PseudoLA_TLS_GD_LARGE: { ----
1182 unsigned Rd = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1183 unsigned Rj = Inst.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1184 if (Rd == Rj) 0
1185 return Match_RequiresLAORdDifferRj; 0
1186 break; 0
1187 } ----
1188 case LoongArch::CSRXCHG: 0
1189 case LoongArch::GCSRXCHG: { ----
1190 unsigned Rj = Inst.getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1191 if (Rj == LoongArch::R0 || Rj == LoongArch::R1) 0
1192 return Match_RequiresOpnd2NotR0R1; 0
1193 return Match_Success; 0
1194 } ----
1195 case LoongArch::BSTRINS_W: 0
1196 case LoongArch::BSTRINS_D: ----
1197 case LoongArch::BSTRPICK_W: ----
1198 case LoongArch::BSTRPICK_D: { ----
1199 unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode(); 0
1200 const signed Msb = ----
1201 (Opc == LoongArch::BSTRINS_W || Opc == LoongArch::BSTRINS_D) 0
1202 ? Inst.getOperand(3).getImm() 0
1203 : Inst.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1204 const signed Lsb = ----
1205 (Opc == LoongArch::BSTRINS_W || Opc == LoongArch::BSTRINS_D) 0
1206 ? Inst.getOperand(4).getImm() 0
1207 : Inst.getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1208 if (Msb < Lsb) 0
1209 return Match_RequiresMsbNotLessThanLsb; 0
1210 return Match_Success; 0
1211 } ----
1212 } ----
1213 ----
1214 return Match_Success; 0
